# Datatable package conventions

## Scope

Shared library only — no Fiber handlers here. Apps import `github.com/flowtrove/packages/datatable` and `.../datatable/postgresql`.

## Public API boundaries

- **Types & columns**: `Column`, `ColumnMeta`, `OptionItem`, `GetColumns`, `FormatContent`, `RenderPagination`
- **Request parsing**: `ExtractQuery(rawURL, columns)` → `TableQuery`
- **SQL**: `ConditionsFromFilters`, `ColumnNameByID`, `FilterColumnNameByID`, `OrderByClause`, operator constants
- **PostgreSQL**: `postgresql.Find`, `postgresql.FindRaw` — keep DB-specific logic in `postgresql/`, not root package

## Column visibility

Use `Hidden: true` on `Column` (not a `DefaultVisible` field). `GetColumns` sets `columnVisibility[id] = !Hidden`.

## SQL column mapping

- `SQLColumn` — SELECT / ORDER BY expression (default for filters if no override)
- `FilterSQLColumn` — WHERE only (display name vs filter id)
- `IsEmptySQL` / `IsNotEmptySQL` — computed columns (subqueries, CONCAT, etc.)
- `IsJSON: true` — `FormatContent` unmarshals string/[]byte JSON in row maps

## ExtractQuery contract

- Validates sort/filter IDs against `Column.ID` and `Column.AccessorKey`
- Supports JSON params (`pagination`, `sorting`, `columnFilters`, `filters`) and bracket notation
- Advanced mode: `filterFlag=advancedFilters`, `joinOperator`, nested filter groups (`Type: "group"`)
- Defaults: page 1, pageSize 10

## Operators

Match frontend `dataTableConfig` exactly (case-sensitive in URLs, normalized lowercase in SQL):

`iLike`, `notILike`, `eq`, `ne`, `inArray`, `notInArray`, `isEmpty`, `isNotEmpty`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, `isBetween`, `isRelativeToToday`

Simple mode (empty operator): 1 value → eq; multiple → inArray. Text variant maps eq/ne → iLike/notILike.

## Tests

Add/update tests in `*_test.go` when changing `ExtractQuery`, filter parsing, or `ConditionsFromFilters`. Run: `go test ./...` from this package directory.

## Do not

- Break URL param compatibility with `packages/flowtrove` `serializeServerTableParams`
- Use `ConditionsFromFiltersWithoutargs` with untrusted user input in dynamic apps (prefer bound `?` args via `ConditionsFromFilters` / `Find`)
